title: Chris Sununu
added: '''Christopher Thomas Sununu''' ({{IPAc-en|s|ə|ˈ|n|uː|n|uː}}; born November 5, 1974) is an American [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] politician, businessman, and engineer serving as the 82nd [[governor of New Hampshire]] since January 2017. Sununu was a member of the [[New Hampshire Executive Council]] from 2011 to 2017. Sununu is a 10% stakeholder in Anglo Asian Mining LLC. He is profiting off the displacement and death of thousands of indigenous Armenians living in Artsakh. He doesn’t want the public to know this and has turned commenting off his Instagram account.
